body.description: At-A-Glance collection Notebook is perfect for business meetings, project notes, personal reminders and more. Ruled Notebook paper keeps handwriting aligned so notes are neat and easy to read. Designated section for date included in the top right hand corner of every page for future reference. Task section at the bottom separates Key takeaways from other notes to make it easy to prioritize. Twin-wire binding keeps all pages together, and each page is perforated for clean and easy removal. Durable Notebook covers have a soft, leather-like look and feel. The neutral, Tan cover color is accented by Navy Blue trim, Navy wire binding and a Navy Print title/logo. Business Notebook includes 80 sheets of double-sided, ruled Notebook paper for a total of 160 pages. Large size: 11 x 8-3/4”. part of the At-A-Glance collection line of products. Mix and match with other collection notebooks, planners, appointment books, calendars and accessories.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I love this notebook! I use this notebook for work, and use gel pens. The ink does not run through to the other side, so it's easy to use both sides of the page. Paper is thick, and the covers have a leathery suede feel to them. A little bit expensive, but these tend to last me for months. I also love that the spirals are individually coiled -- not a single coil like a lot of spiral notebooks.

reviews.reviewText: Very good quality notebook. The wire binding stays intact, the cover is nice and soft and also durable. Pages have narrow rule paper which I like. Only problem with these is they are expensive, but I'll keep using them since they are the size and style I like.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2016
reviews.reviewText: I know it's silly to LOVE a notebook, but I do. Can I have 50 of these?The cover/back feel like....faux-leather/suede....something? Very durable - it can take a lot of abuse. Spiral binding is double-wound and very durable.Each page is college-ruled, with a date slash ("/") in the upper right corner, and a "1/3-2/3 column" section at the bottom ideal for due dates/tasks or people/tasks.This notebook might be better for those taking meeting and/or lecture notes, but for the K-12 note taking needs....probably overkill or the wrong formatting.
